ich document commonly proves program completion for a PGWP?","options":["A completion letter or final transcript","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Applicants commonly use school-issued completion evidence to prove they finished the program."},{"level":1,"question":"What mainly determines the possible length of a PGWP?","options":["The length and eligibility of the completed study program","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"PGWP validity is tied mainly to eligible program length, subject to policy limits."},{"level":1,"question":"What does DLI mean in PGWP planning?","options":["Designated Learning Institution","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"A DLI is approved to host international students, but not every DLI program supports a PGWP."},{"level":1,"question":"When does a student usually become eligible to apply for a PGWP?","options":["After receiving confirmation that the eligible program is complete","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"The application is tied to program completion, not simply attending classes."},{"level":1,"question":"Is a job offer normally required for a PGWP application?","options":["No, a PGWP usually does not require a job offer","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Because it is open, the PGWP is not normally based on a specific employer offer."},{"level":1,"question":"What is the usual maximum PGWP duration under standard rules?","options":["Up to three years","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA ap