 apply for PR card. Meet residency obligations for citizenship pathway."},{"q":"Is Eligible program (FSW/CEC/FST) required?","a":"Eligible program (FSW/CEC/FST) is typically required."},{"q":"Is Language test (CLB minimum per program) required?","a":"Language test (CLB minimum per program) is typically required."},{"q":"Is ECA for foreign credentials (FSW) required?","a":"WES/IQAS etc."},{"q":"Is CRS score competitive for recent draws required?","a":"Assess against recent cutoffs"},{"q":"Is Work experience documented (NOC/TEER) required?","a":"Work experience documented (NOC/TEER) is typically required."},{"q":"Is Proof of funds (FSW/ FST if applicable) required?","a":"Proof of funds (FSW/ FST if applicable) is typically required."},{"q":"Is Medical and police completed after ITA required?","a":"Assess whether Medical and police completed after ITA is satisfied for this case."},{"q":"What is the Processing time?","a":"6–12m — After ITA received"},{"q":"What is the Government fee?","a":"CAD $1,525+ — PR application after ITA"},{"q":"What is the Our approval rate?","a":"94% — ~88% post-ITA benchmark"},{"q":"What is the Required docs?","a":"16 — + ECA, language, work ref"},{"q":"What is the Consultancy fee?","a":"See fee tab — + govt & ECA/tests"},{"q":"What if the client has CRS below recent draw cutoffs?","a":"Retake language for higher CLB; pursue PNP; gain Canadian work experience"},{"q":"Why is CRS below recent draw cutoffs a problem?","a":"Client expects ITA with non-competitive score."},{"q":"What if the client has Wrong NOC/TEER code?","a":"Verify TEER category against official duties and reference letters"},{"q":"Why is Wrong NOC/TEER code a problem?","a":"Work experience coded incorrectly affecting points."}],"compliance":["Client service agreement and consent must be on file before submission","Never guarantee visa or immigration approval; use approved-language only","Fee quotes must separate consultancy, government, and third-party costs","Paid RCIC represe